<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870921-0159 </DOCNO><HL> Allegheny Beverage BoostsDebenture Buy-Back Offer</HL><DD> 09/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ABEVBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> CHEVERLY, Md.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Allegheny Beverage Corp. increased its offer to buy-back any and all of its 9 1/2% convertible debentures due 2010 to a price of 105 from 100 and extended the offer to 12:01 a.m. Oct. 2 from Sept. 28.    The food service concern said only about $4.8 million of the $105 million outstanding had been tendered as of Friday. Holders who already tendered their debentures will receive the higher price, the company said. The offer is contingent upon completion of the proposed sale of Allegheny's Service America Corp. unit. </TEXT></DOC>